12/23/2022,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,02/07/2023,02/03/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,A caregiver escalated an altercation between two children when the caregiver threatened the children with a knife. ,"CORRECTIVE ACTION PLAN
Kazahs Emergency Shelter

This investigation stemmed from a case whereby a staff member threatened with the use of a weapon on children in care. It is worth emphasizing that the staff was immediately taken off from the roll of active employees and has no more access to our facility or to any of our children in care. Because of this incident, we, at Kazahs Emergency Shelter, shall be implementing the following Corrective Action Plan.

1. Service Plans of all children in care will be thoroughly reviewed and implemented in accordance with its contents. The service plans will be explained to caregivers with the expectation that the caregivers shall fully understand and acknowledge the same. A review of the service plans shall be done routinely as scheduled in coordination with CPS, caseworkers, and other stakeholders.

2. Kazahs Emergency Shelter shall conduct a reorientation and re-training of all staff and caregivers concerning the exercise of prudent judgment in the care of children. The re-orientation and re-training shall center on self-control and prudent judgment, taking into consideration the welfare and safety of children in care. Once the re-orientation and re-training is finished, a documentation of the activity will be forwarded to the Licensing Rep. Also, Kazahs Emergency Shelter will regularly and routinely administer this re-orientation and re-training to staff and caregivers.

3. Kazahs Emergency Shelter shall hold training for staff and caregivers in relation to crisis situations, keeping in mind the respect of children's rights to be free from abuse, neglect, or exploitation or exposing children to the risk of physical injury.

This Corrective Action Plan shall take effect and be implemented immediately and proper documentation shall be forwarded to the Licensing Rep."
12/23/2022,748.685(c)(6) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,02/07/2023,02/03/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,Yes,A caregiver failed to follow three children's service plans when the caregiver left the children alone in the operation. ,"CORRECTIVE ACTION PLAN
Kazahs Emergency Shelter

This investigation stemmed from a case whereby a staff member threatened with the use of a weapon on children in care. It is worth emphasizing that the staff was immediately taken off from the roll of active employees and has no more access to our facility or to any of our children in care. Because of this incident, we, at Kazahs Emergency Shelter, shall be implementing the following Corrective Action Plan.

1. Service Plans of all children in care will be thoroughly reviewed and implemented in accordance with its contents. The service plans will be explained to caregivers with the expectation that the caregivers shall fully understand and acknowledge the same. A review of the service plans shall be done routinely as scheduled in coordination with CPS, caseworkers, and other stakeholders.

2. Kazahs Emergency Shelter shall conduct a reorientation and re-training of all staff and caregivers concerning the exercise of prudent judgment in the care of children. The re-orientation and re-training shall center on self-control and prudent judgment, taking into consideration the welfare and safety of children in care. Once the re-orientation and re-training is finished, a documentation of the activity will be forwarded to the Licensing Rep. Also, Kazahs Emergency Shelter will regularly and routinely administer this re-orientation and re-training to staff and caregivers.

3. Kazahs Emergency Shelter shall hold training for staff and caregivers in relation to crisis situations, keeping in mind the respect of children's rights to be free from abuse, neglect, or exploitation or exposing children to the risk of physical injury.

This Corrective Action Plan shall take effect and be implemented immediately and proper documentation shall be forwarded to the Licensing Rep."
